            limitedUse: null,
            name: 'Metamagic - Twinned Spell',
            description:
              '<p class="Core-Styles_Core-Body">When you cast a spell that targets only one creature and doesn&rsquo;t have a range of self, you can spend a number of sorcery points equal to the spell&rsquo;s level to target a second creature in range with the same spell (1 sorcery point if the spell i<span class="No-Break">s a cantrip).</span></p>\r\n<p class="Core-Styles_Core-Body">To be eligible, a spell must be incapable of targeting more than one creature at the spell&rsquo;s current level. For example, [spell]<span class="Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif">magic missile[/spell]</span>&nbsp;and [spell]<span class="Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif">scorching ray[/spell]</span>&nbsp;aren&rsquo;t eligible, but [spell]<span class="Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif">ray of frost[/spell]</span>&nbsp;and [spell]<span class="Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif">chrom</span><span class="No-Break"><span class="Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif">atic orb[/spell]</span></span><span class="No-Break">&nbsp;are.</span></p>',
